    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Shelves or the Web?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Matt Hillletter on selling books to other individuals on line (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The News Watch report on the used-book market said that ''recent mass-market romance paperbacks are all but unavailable on the Web.'' Lest one should think that the e-gods have failed readers, simply check out www.half.com, where individuals can sell books to other individuals. Popular mass-market paperbacks typically sell for about a dollar, plus $1.58 for shipping. There is no shortage.</p>
        <p>MATT HILL  Yonkers, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
